<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>You're distorting my position anyway. I'm not stating that it is categorically unethical to eat living things, only that any enjoyment we get out of meat over vegetables isn't worth animal suffering. In no way does a weak position that plant suffering is possible make a strong case for animal suffering inadmissable to our eating choices. That's simply absurd.</font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=400></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3014398 href="vote?for=3014398&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%46%43%79%31%68%49%43%4e%48%31"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3014398></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=jodrellblank">jodrellblank</a> 138 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3014398">link</a></span></div><br>
